    <TD rowspan="2" vAlign=top>
    	<table cellPadding=5 width="100%" border="0" bgcolor="#FOE68C"><TR><TD align=left><font color="#006699" face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2"><B>WHO'S HIRING</B></font><BR><a name="vwLJLMHKHPHIx"></a>
<a href="http://people.venturewire.com/feature.asp?sid=LJLMHKHPHI"><font face="verdana, arial, geneva, helvetica" size="2"><b>Zambeel of Fremont, Calif. </b></font></a><BR><font face="verdana, arial, geneva, helvetica" color="black" size="1"><i>By <a href="mailto:greenwood@venturewire.com">Giselle Greenwood</a></i></font><BR><font face="verdana, arial, geneva, helvetica" color="black" size="1">Even though Zambeel, a provider of enterprise-class data management and storage platform, hasn&#39;t officially launched yet, the company has already grown from 85 employees at the beginning of the year to 120 and it isn&#39;t stopping there. Zambeel plans to continue expanding with the additions of several technical staff.<br><br>Vice president of human resources, Bill Hammack, says the company needs to beef up the technical side of its business more than ever due to an upcoming beta trial scheduled for the end of the year and the commercial launch of its technology in the first half !
of next year. As the company gets closer to commercial launch, Mr. Hammack says it will also add infrastructure people, including sales, customer support, and operations staff.<br><br>Despite its pre-launch status, Mr. Hammack says the company hasn&#39;t had a problem attracting the type of candidates it looks for -- senior level people with experience in the storage space.<br><br>"I believe senior level is a function of experience, not age," Mr. Hammack says.</font><a href="http://people.venturewire.com/feature.asp?sid=LJLMHKHPHI"><font face="verdana, arial, geneva, helvetica" size="1">>></font></a><BR>
</TD></TR></TABLE><br><table cellPadding=5 width="100%" border="0"><TR bgcolor="#FOE68C"><TD align=left vAlign=top><FONT color="006699" face="verdana, arial,  helvetica" size=-1><B>EXECUTIVE SEARCHES</B></FONT><BR><font color=black face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size=-2>&#8226; <a href="#clsfd1185">VP, MARKETING-SILICON VALLEY</a><BR>&#8226; <a href="#clsfd1184">DIRECTOR, BUSINESS DEVELOPMENT-ANY MAJOR METRO AREA IN NORTHEAST</a><BR>&#8226; <a href="#clsfd1182">VICE PRESIDENT, MARKETING-FREMONT, CA</a><BR></font></TD></TR></table><br>
